Explore the SDK's command line tools:
Most useful command:
- android - open the standalone Android SDK manager
- android avd - open eclipse version of Android Manager
- android list avd - Display listing of all existing virtual devices.
- emulator -avd <device name> - open a new virtual device
- avd devices - list all the connected devices
-----------------
Manipulate the device:
- adb reboot - reboot the device
- monitor - present a device view, where we can find
              - Threads
              - Heap
              - Allocation Tracker
              - network Statics
              - File Explorer

- Command to create a new Android Project

android create project --target 1 --name MyAndroidApp --path ./MyAndroidApProject
--activity MainActivity --package com.example.myandroidapp
